race.comment: STROMBOLI DELIGHT (14) has been safely held in two runs since returning from a spell, both at Doomben. Has switched to the Pat Webster camp since that last run and finds an easier maiden this time. Can improve enough to play a significant role. UPSTART LOVER (15) needed more ground last time out when sixth over 1100m at this track. Blinkers on and strips fitter so over an extra 100m this evening she comes right into calculations. CHOCECLAIR (12) encountered a soft track and didn't fire last start when lining up for the first time under new trainer Sharon Croxford. Can do better on firmer footing this time. ATTACK FORCE (6) changed stables prior to his eye-catching third over this trip at Kilcoy recently. Should take a lot from that run, the first in 38 days. Respect any market support for DEFYING (18) who is first-up for 170 days and is now with the Mark Currie yard.
